40.0,"enterprise_to_ebitda":512.604,"enterprise_to_revenue":12.378,"shares_outstanding":4936470.0,"float_shares":859397.0,"held_pct_insiders":0.83741,"held_pct_institutions":0.0,"beta":-0.108,"fifty_two_week_high":88.6,"fifty_two_week_low":38.28182,"fifty_day_average":59.83458,"two_hundred_day_avg":67.891464,"recommendation":"none","all_time_high":94.50909,"all_time_low":1.472726,"long_business_summary":"Accedere Limited provides cybersecurity services in India. The company offers system and organization controls (SOC) reporting services; SOC 1 and SOC 2 type 2 compliance audit; SOC reports for cloud security, privacy, and cyber risk; and SOC for supply chain. It also provides ISO/IEC certifications for data security and privacy; cloud CSA STAR audits as empanelled by cloud security alliance; vulnerability assessment and pentest services; security operations center; and training services. In addition, the company offers US federal, India CERT-in, and Mena and Europe compliance assessments; cloud security assessments; privacy assessments; supervisory control and data acquisition services; breach and attack simulation; and ESG services, as well as CSOC services. Further, it offers Controllo, an AI-driven compliance automation platform for compliance and automate risk management. Additionally, the company offers unmanned aircraft systems providing actionable intelligence from aerial data under the brand Freebird, which serves defense and homeland security sector. The company was formerly known as E Com Infotech (India) Limited and changed its name to Accedere Limited in September 2020. Accedere Limited was incorporated in 1983 and is based in Mumbai, India."}}